content.text:
Perfect! I've identified and fixed the architectural issue. Here's what was happening:

## The Problem: Architectural Issue in FloatingPanel

The `FloatingPanel` component had **hardcoded click-outside-to-close behavior** with no way to disable it. Looking at lines 547-558, it always set up the `onClickOutside` listener that called `handleClose()`:

```typescript
// BEFORE: Always closes on click outside
onClickOutside(elementRef, (event) => {
  // ... ignore class checks ...
  handleClose()  // Always called!
}, { ignore: [] })
```

There was no prop in the Props interface to disable this behavior - it was always active.

## The Solution: Added `closeOnClickOutside` Prop

I've made **two architectural improvements** to FloatingPanel.vue:

### 1. Added new prop with backward compatibility
```typescript
interface Props {
  // ...
  closeOnClickOutside?: boolean  // Close panel when clicking outside (default: true)
  // ...
}

// Default to true for backward compatibility
const props = withDefaults(defineProps<Props>(), {
  // ...
  closeOnClickOutside: true
})
```

### 2. Made click-outside listener conditional
```typescript
// AFTER: Only set up listener if enabled
if (props.closeOnClickOutside) {
  onClickOutside(elementRef, (event) => {
    // ... ignore class checks ...
    handleClose()
  }, { ignore: [] })
}
```

### 3. Updated ContactUsFloating to disable click-outside
```vue
<FloatingPanel
  :close-on-click-outside="false"
  <!-- ... other props ... -->
>
```

## Result

Now the floating contact form:
- ✅ **Stays open when clicking the landing page** behind it
- ✅ Users can scroll, read content, interact with other elements
- ✅ Only closes via the X button or Cancel button
- ✅ Still draggable and resizable
- ✅ Backward compatible - all existing FloatingPanel uses still close on click-outside by default

This was definitely an architectural gap in FloatingPanel that needed fixing. The component was designed with modal-like behavior but didn't provide flexibility for true floating panel use cases!

